==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Ethiopic
<hw>E`thi*op"ic</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The language of ancient
Ethiopia; the language of the ancient Abyssinian empire (in Ethiopia),
now used only in the Abyssinian church. It is of Semitic origin, and is
also called <altname>Geez</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ethiops</ent>⟦br⟧
